{"questionId":"9997","questionHtml":"<p>If&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"A = \\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  {2p}&amp;3 \\\\   { - 4p}&amp;p  \\end{array}} \\right)\">\n  <mi>A</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mn>2</mn>\n              <mi>p</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>3</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mn>4</mn>\n              <mi>p</mi>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n          <mtd>\n            <mi>p</mi>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> and det <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"A = 14\">\n  <mi>A</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>14</mn>\n</math></span>,&nbsp;find the possible values of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"p\">\n  <mi>p</mi>\n</math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"color:#999;font-size:90%;font-style:italic;\">* This question is from an exam for a previous syllabus, and may contain minor differences in marking or structure.</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"2{p^2} + 12p = 14\">\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>p</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>12</mn>\n  <mi>p</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>14</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em><em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"{p^2} + 6p - 7 = 0\">\n  <mrow>\n    <msup>\n      <mi>p</mi>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n    </msup>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>6</mn>\n  <mi>p</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>7</mn>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {p + 7} \\right)\\left( {p - 1} \\right) = 0\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>p</mi>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>7</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>p</mi>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mn>1</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>0</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"p =&nbsp; - 7\">\n  <mi>p</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>7</mn>\n</math></span> or&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"p = 1\">\n  <mi>p</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)&nbsp;(C4)</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note: </strong>Both answers are required for the final <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em>.</p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9997","referenceCode":"EXM.1.AHL.TZ0.2","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"If A = ( 2 p 3 − 4 p p ) and det A = 14 , find the possible values of p .","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"2","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.14—Introduction to matrices"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}